@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1 class="text-center">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <p>
            Welcome to the Library Management System. Your privacy is of utmost importance to us,
            and we are committed to safeguarding the personal information you provide while using our platform.
            This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you access
            and interact with our system.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
            We collect personal information necessary for the operation of the Library Management System. This may include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Your name, email address, and contact information during user registration.</li>
            <li>Book transaction details, such as borrowing and return dates.</li>
            <li>Technical information, such as IP address, browser type, and usage logs.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>
            The information we collect is used for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>To provide library services, including book searches, borrowing, and returning.</li>
            <li>To notify users about overdue books or system updates.</li>
            <li>To improve system performance and user experience through analytics.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. How We Protect Your Information</h2>
        <p>
            We are committed to ensuring that your personal information is secure. To prevent unauthorized access, we implement industry-standard security measures, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Encryption of sensitive data.</li>
            <li>Regular system updates and vulnerability assessments.</li>
            <li>Access controls to limit data access to authorized personnel only.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Sharing Your Information</h2>
        <p>
            We do not sell or share your personal information with third parties, except when required by law or with your explicit consent. In some cases, we may share anonymized data for research or analytics purposes.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
            As a user of the Library Management System, you have the following rights:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>To access and update your personal information through your account settings.</li>
            <li>To request the deletion of your data, subject to legal and operational constraints.</li>
            <li>To opt out of certain notifications or communications.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be communicated through the system or via email. Continued use of the system signifies your acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
            If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <p>Email: support@librarymanagementsystem.com</p>
        <p>Phone: 013-6779245</p>
    </div>
</body>